description: From Latin fūniculus (“cord”), diminutive from fūnis (“cord”) + -culus.

entries.meaning: (botany) The stalk or stem of an ovule or seed.
examples: The elaiosome emerges from the funicle.

entries.meaning: (entomology) Intermediate segments of the antenna of chalcid wasps adjoining the pedicel basally and the clava distally.
